</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-09-02-0376-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-02-09-02-0376-fn-0001">1</a>

   <p>On 8 Mar. GW left for Berkeley, Fauquier, and Loudoun counties to deal with his tenants and to inspect the Mercers Bull Run Mountains land
<span class="pb" title="page number in print edition (no page scan available)" id="GEWN-02-09-02-pb-0508">[508]</span>
which was to be divided up in preparation for the sale of George Mercers portion in November. GW returned to Mount Vernon on 20 March. See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-09-02-0385" class="document">Riddell to GW, 2, 18 Mar.</a>, and <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-09-02-0378" class="document">GW to Riddell, 5 March.</a></p>

</div>
